CatDescriptText: Miss Cecilia Trower, 2720 Wylie Avenue, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 25, 1958, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that business and employment are as good as the Eisenhower administration declares that it is?" answer reads: "I feel that business is picking up no more than during the past two or three weeks. I'm talking of the Pittsburgh area and not generally for the whole country, because I am not too well informed on nation-wide economic conditions."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Cecelia Trower wearing eyeglasses, floral blouse, and flecked coat, holding spiral notebook and dark handbag, standing on sidewalk in front of street with buildings, including one with sign that reads "Elect"
